At the 17k mark, it was clear that I was heading into heat stroke territory.

I had done that to myself before in the past and I knew the recovery cost. With Covid, it was going to be worse

It didn't take long to make the decision, call for help and get picked up from the track.

A lesson from a different life.

My last half marathon was 2 month after recovering from Covid-19.

I had trained hard for it, felt great heading into it. 

The first 10k was on track but rather than hitting the wall at the 17k mark, I hit it at 12k.

I did not finish (DNF).
